metadata.othernotes:
Summary
- Young fighter pilot for a spacecraft. Subteam leader/second-in-command under Meia; pilots are around their age (high school/college).
- Pirate crew. ~100-150 women, 3 male prisoners.
- Home planet Mejare, Earth colony. Population is all female. Women form couples and families there, having children together. Jura's biological parents (and those of all her crewmates) were, implicitly, both women.
- Mejare is at war with neighboring planet, all-male Tarak. Each does not see the other sex as human.
- Other colonies exist with other societies. Earth has been attacking colonies to harvest colonists' organs.
- Probably wealthy as a child, like many of her crewmates.
- Mejare is a fleet nation, having failed to properly terraform the surface for some time, to the "empire's" embarrassment. Its cities are built in ships orbiting the planet. It is unlikely that Jura has ever lived on a planet's surface for any significant amount of time.

Personality
- Vain and self-absorbed. Carefully maintains her appearance. Wants attention for her beauty and strength (as a fighter pilot).
- Beautiful and she knows it. Feels "you don't lose anything by being seen," and loves to be admired.
- Loves anything she perceives as "elegant" or powerful, including imagined scenarios.
- Liable to whine and complain when things don't go her way or as she envisioned. Has a childish way of speaking when she's too distraught to project maturity.
- Very open with her feelings, announcing interest and voicing displeasure. Heaps physical affection onto people she likes. Considers her embrace a reward unto itself.
- Not afraid to flirt or flex her looks to get what she wants.
- DOES take her job seriously, despite her high-strung attitude. Worries about cracking under pressure or failing to live up to expectations. Lacks leadership experience.
- Sensitive beneath her bluster. Often lets the more tenacious Barnette, her girlfriend, take charge in dangerous situations. Likes being protected, hates being lonely.
- Following from this, Jura is charmed by serious, steadfast, jealous types, and prefers people who are clean and pretty.
- Brought a sidearm, her sword. Has reservations about Earthlings' trustworthiness.
- "When I want something, I do it." Willing to insert herself into others' social lives and fix their problems, either by announcing them directly or hatching schemes. Can be quite supportive in this way.
- Wants to learn more about men. Believes becoming pregnant by a man's seed---the first Mejarian to do so---will make her famous. Sex with men is a separate but also fascinating prospect. She has not realized the connection between these things.
- Attracted to other girls, obviously. Has a reputation for taking initiative in this regard.
- Still wary of men if given reason; pushy with her peers, but more respectful to those older than her.

Good Topics/Touchstones
- Men's anatomy/physiology/behavior/desires (e.g. no periods, they like big breasts)
- Male/female relationships, experience (e.g. Jura has no concept of birth control)
- any flight/space travel/combat experience or technology unique to your character's setting
- beauty, fashion, and body image
- pregnancy/marriage/family
- diet/exercise/combat training, especially swordplay
- info about Earth, what it's like to live there
- positive F-F relationships/interest
- general questions about Mejare, her rank, ship, crew, etc. (anything that lets her brag about herself)

Bad/Overdone Topics
- "How do two women make babies?" Gene splicing. Normal pregnancy.
- "Your sword/dress/clothes are really advanced!" They're not, even by our standards.
- "omg u r an alien" She's a human.
- Don't treat her like a loredump machine. Ask something that your character would have an opinion on the answer to.
- her past (there's not much canon info)

Barnette
- Jura is accompanied by her girlfriend, Barnette Orangello. Barnette is a fellow pilot on Jura's subteam and also helps manage the ship's weapon stock and delivery system ("Regisystem"). She is much more aggressive and irritable, being fairly humorless and unwilling to play cards. (She also doesn't know how.) She spends the game patrolling the surroundings, but occasionally appears to react to something or speak to Jura. You can target her directly if you wish.
- Despite not always sharing interests, Jura and Barnette are attached at the hip and haunt the ship's halls together. Just as Jura often relies on Barnette to take charge in combat, Barnette usually defers to Jura for socializing.
- Barnette likes to collect antique guns---that is to say, modern guns. Her personal favorite sidearm is her CZ 75 pistol, but she also owns a variety of heavier weapons and looks for any excuse to bust them out. Weapon storage was her family's business before she was forced into piracy.
- She is also a talented cook and frequently bakes cakes and sweets, having taken care of multiple sisters growing up. Between the two of them, Barnette is generally more independent, and Jura more clingy.
- Despite sometimes feeling exasperated by Jura's schemes and antics, Barnette is also genuinely in love and can just as easily fangirl over her. She often captures Jura's beauty and showmanship on film, at her behest, and wants to be the Oma (egg donator) to Jura's baby.
- Barnette seems to have little interest in men and once gained a reputation for being particularly harsh towards their prisoners. But if Jura is fascinated by something, it doesn't take much to get her to follow along.
- Barnette's stated age is 18 in canon material, but the implied timeline of the series puts her at 19 here.
- Instead of masturbating, Jura calls upon Barnette to have sex with her, and responds in kind. Barnette cums before Jura does, 20 ticks in. While they don't completely ignore everyone else, their pillow talk is extremely lovey-dovey and melodramatic. (In general, feel free to target how obnoxious the two of them can be, even earlier on.)

Misc.
- Any character capable of sensing supernatural or psychic power should detect a faint aura around her, enough to raise an eyebrow. This is because:
- Jura pilots a transformed Dread (gunship) and a super robot fusion mech called a Vandread. Both are the result of contact with their main ship's "Paksis" fusion core.
- The Paksis is otherworldly and also granted Jura a mild psychic link with some of her crewmates who shared the experience. Their transformed ships draw power from this sort of spiritual energy (ki) that the pilots put out.
- Jura prefers a defensive, supportive approach to combat. This is reflected in her Vandread's shielding capabilities.
- After finishing, Jura puts her boots back on and then briefly falls asleep with Barnette.
